title: 25 Things You Missed In The Mummy

media:group.media:title: 25 Things You Missed In The Mummy
media:group.media:description:
Subscribe: http://bit.ly/Subscribe-to-Screenrant

Grab your first class tickets for the Fraser-train, we’re hopping aboard and traveling 23 years into the past to explore the movie that bears the most responsibility for launching Brendan Fraser’s stellar yet tumultuous career, no offense to our fellow George of the Jungle stans. In a year that marked some of the most exciting cinematic releases - the Matrix, The Sixth Sense, Star Wars Episode 1 and more - 1999 was packed to the brim with films we still hold dear to this day. Sure, The Matrix had Keanu, the Sixth Sense had Brucey Dubs, and Star Wars had Jar Jar (meant to be sarcastic ;), but Universal Pictures’ The Mummy had a secret ingredient far superior. Forget maple syrup, Canada’s sweetest export has always been Brendan Freaking Fraser.
